parsed.explanation: Corrected multiple character encoding errors that garbled German umlauts and other special characters (e.g., '√§' to 'ä', '√†' to 'à'). Fixed the place name 'St. Elübethen' to the more likely 'St. Elisabethen'. Repaired the invalid XML structure where the <TITLE> tag was improperly closed and then closed again; the descriptive text was merged into a single, long title, which is characteristic of the era. The non-standard <PRIZE> tag was renamed to the more semantic <PRICE>.
